## Path predicate decision matrix

This is the most-litigated decision in WAF reviews. Use this matrix; document the choice in the inline comment.

| Choice | Use when | Bypass surface | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `http.request.uri.path eq "/api/x"` | The legitimate flow is **only** the bare endpoint, requester confirmed | Narrowest | Future child paths under `/api/x/*` continue to be evaluated by OWASP - this is a defense-in-depth feature, not a coverage gap. Use this by default. |
| `starts_with(http.request.uri.path, "/api/x/")` (with trailing slash) | Many child paths under `/api/x/` are legitimate (e.g., Streamlit `/_stcore/upload_file/<id>`) | Broad - covers all sub-paths | Always include the trailing slash to avoid matching `/api/x-export`, `/api/x-v2` siblings. |
| `(eq "/api/x" or starts_with("/api/x/"))` (alternation) | Both bare endpoint AND child paths are legitimate | Broad + bare | Use when the requester explicitly wants both. |
| `starts_with(http.request.uri.path, "/api/x")` (no trailing slash) | **NEVER** | Accidentally broad | Matches `/api/x-export`, `/api/x-v2`, `/api/xrelease`. This is a known anti-pattern - reject in review. |

> [!CAUTION]
> Title, body, provenance artifact, and the saved rule expression must all agree on the predicate shape. Past changes have had to be redone when the title said "broaden" but the saved expression used `eq`. Treat all four as a single source of truth - update them together or don't update at all.
>
> Per-interface mapping:
>
> - **Terraform:** PR title + PR body + HCL `#` comment + the expression in HCL.
> - **Dashboard:** change ticket title + change ticket body + runbook entry + the expression in the UI's expression editor.
> - **API:** PR title + PR body in the JSON repo + the sibling `.md` provenance file + the `expression` field in the JSON.

