## Anti-patterns (reject in review)

These have all shown up in past WAF PRs (observed in the wild). If you see one, request changes.

### Shared (all interfaces, both rule types)

1. **`starts_with(http.request.uri.path, "/api/x")` without trailing slash** - matches sibling paths like `/api/x-export`. Either add the trailing slash or use `eq`.
2. **Title-vs-code drift** - in Terraform: PR title says "broaden" but code says `eq`. In Dashboard: change-ticket says "broaden" but the saved rule uses `eq`. In API: PR description for the JSON payload says "broaden" but the JSON says `eq`. All four sources of truth (title, body, provenance artifact, code / payload / saved rule) must agree.
3. **Hardcoded IPs** instead of `$trusted_egress_ips` (or its API equivalent: a named [IP List](https://developers.cloudflare.com/waf/tools/lists/)). The named list is centrally maintained; hardcoding stale IPs is how you DoS yourself in six months.
4. **Plain `http.request.headers["X"] eq "..."`** - wrong syntax for a multi-value header field. Use `any(http.request.headers["X"][*] eq "...")`.
5. **Single-value content-type check** - `http.request.headers["content-type"] eq "multipart/form-data"` is wrong syntax and wrong semantics (header is multi-value, may include `; boundary=...`). Use `any(lower(http.request.headers["content-type"][*])[*] contains "multipart/form-data")`.
6. **Outer parens wrapping a top-level `and` chain** - `(a and b and c)`. The parens are a no-op; remove them for readability.
7. **Missing provenance** - every WAF rule (custom or skip) is a policy commitment. Whether the provenance carrier is an HCL `#` comment (Terraform), a runbook entry (Dashboard), or a sibling `.md` (API), the rule does not merge / save / `PUT` without it.
8. **No `log`-mode soak before enforce** - new block / skip rules should be staged in `action = "log"` (or Dashboard "Log" action / API `"action": "log"`) for at least 24h to validate the predicate hits the intended traffic shape, then promoted to `block` / `skip`.

### Managed-Rule Exceptions only

<!-- markdownlint-disable MD029 -->
<!-- Numbering continues from the Shared section above so reviewers can reference "anti-pattern #N" unambiguously. -->

9. **Skip applied to whole managed ruleset** when only specific child rules fire - over-broad. List the specific rule IDs in `action_parameters.rules[ruleset_id]` (Terraform / API) or "Skip specific rules" in the Dashboard UI.
10. **Skip rule placed AFTER the `execute` rule** - has no effect. `skip` only applies to `execute` rules listed after it. Cloudflare doc is explicit: ["Rules with `skip` action only apply to rules with `execute` action listed after them."](https://developers.cloudflare.com/waf/managed-rules/waf-exceptions/define-api/) In the Dashboard, drag the skip rule above the execute rule; in API, use `position.before` with the execute rule's ID; in Terraform, list the skip rule earlier in the `rules` block.
11. **Multipart skip without `filename=` body marker** - matches POSTs with multipart content-type but no actual file part.

### Custom Rules only

12. **Block rule placed BEFORE the corresponding allow-skip rule** - the block fires first, the allow never gets a chance. Allow-before-block ordering is non-negotiable.
13. **Geo block without trusted-egress escape hatch** - blocks legitimate users in transit. Always include `or ip.src in $trusted_egress_ips` (or equivalent named source list).
14. **`js_challenge` on `/api/*` paths** - breaks API and CLI clients. Use `managed_challenge` for ambiguous traffic, or scope the rule to non-API paths.
15. **Country-code typos** - country lists like `{"US" "CA" "MX" "GB"}` are case-sensitive ISO-3166 alpha-2. Always paste from the [Cloudflare country code reference](https://developers.cloudflare.com/network/country-codes/), never type from memory.

### Terraform-specific (only when authoring HCL)

16. **Description prefixed with the ticket ID** - the `description` field is for what the rule *does*; put the ticket in the inline `//` comment block. (Existing rules with ticket-prefixed names should be kept as-is - the Dashboard / log history references them.)
17. **Outer parens wrapping a top-level `and` chain** in HCL - already in Shared #6, but worth restating since HCL is forgiving.
18. **Heredoc body indented inconsistently with the neighboring rule** - `<<-EOT` strips the shortest leading-whitespace prefix, so semantically a no-op, but it makes diffs noisy. Match the surrounding rule's indent.
19. **File mode flipped to `100755`** on a `.tf` file - trips `check-executables-have-shebangs` pre-commit. Restore to `100644`.
20. **Dashboard / API edits not ported back to Terraform** - causes `terraform plan` drift and silent override of peer review. See "Source-of-truth discipline" callout near the top.

### Dashboard-specific (only when authoring via the UI)

21. **Editing a live rule without first cloning it to a staging rule** - no rollback path if the new expression mis-fires. Clone, edit the clone in log mode, validate, then disable the original and enable the clone.
22. **Saving without recording the change in your team's runbook** - Audit Logs tell you *who / what / when* but never *why*. The runbook is your only `why` carrier in Dashboard authoring; missing entries make rules un-auditable.
23. **Using bulk-edit / drag-to-reorder without a separate change ticket per logical change** - bulk Dashboard saves are recorded as one Audit Log entry. If three semantically distinct changes ship in one save, debugging which one broke production is harder than it needs to be.
24. **Authoring directly in production zone without a staging-zone dry-run** - Dashboard has no `terraform plan` equivalent. The dry-run is "save in zone-staging in log mode, observe 24h, then re-author in zone-prod".

### API-specific (only when calling the Rulesets API directly)

25. **Partial `PATCH` without fetching current state first** - the API supports rule-by-rule `PATCH`, but concurrent edits from another tool / human will race. Always `GET` the current ruleset, modify, `PUT` the whole thing with an `If-Match` ETag header to detect concurrent writes.
26. **Hard-coding `position.index`** instead of `position.before` / `position.after` with a stable rule ID. Index-based positioning breaks the moment anyone else inserts a rule above; ID-relative positioning survives.
27. **Calling the API without recording the change** in a versioned JSON repo or run-log. Without it, there's no provenance, no review trail, and no way to bulk-rollback.
28. **Validating the JSON payload only at `PUT` time** - the API returns errors but at that point you've already attempted the change. Run the JSON through [Cloudflare's expression test endpoint](https://developers.cloudflare.com/ruleset-engine/rulesets-api/test/) (`POST /test`) before the destructive `PUT`.
29. **Skipping ETag / `If-Match` on writes** - lets concurrent writers silently clobber each other. Always send `If-Match: <etag>` on `PUT` / `PATCH`; handle 412 Precondition Failed by re-fetching and re-applying intent.

