## Reviewer checklist (copy into PR description / change ticket)

### Shared (always check, regardless of interface)

- [ ] Cloudflare docs have been re-read for this change (WAF custom rules / WAF exceptions / ruleset-engine fields, plus OWASP CRS reference if it's a managed-rule skip)
- [ ] `description` field is purpose-based, not ticket-prefixed (Terraform) or includes the ticket suffix per the per-zone convention (Dashboard / API)
- [ ] Peer rule in the same zone has been identified (cross-referenced in the provenance artifact)
- [ ] Path predicate choice (`eq` vs `starts_with` with-trailing-slash vs alternation) matches requester intent and is documented
- [ ] All four sources of truth agree (PR / ticket title, PR / ticket body, provenance artifact, saved rule / code / JSON)
- [ ] Multi-value headers use `any(... [*] ...)` form (not bare `eq`)
- [ ] Content-type guard (where used) uses `any(lower(...)[*] contains ...)` form
- [ ] No hardcoded IPs - `$trusted_egress_ips` / a named IP List referenced
- [ ] No outer parens wrapping the top-level `and` chain
- [ ] Action choice is documented in the provenance artifact (why `block` vs `managed_challenge` vs `skip`)
- [ ] Provenance artifact present and complete (ticket, peer cross-reference, per-guard rationale, approval source, review-by date)
- [ ] New block- / skip-class rules went through a `log`-mode soak (linked in PR / ticket) before being promoted
- [ ] Source-of-truth discipline respected: change made via the zone's documented authoring path

### Managed-Rule Exceptions only

- [ ] OWASP child-rule list is the established baseline - additions justified per incident
- [ ] Skip rule positioned BEFORE the `execute` rule it bypasses (Terraform: earlier in `rules`; Dashboard: drag above; API: `position.before` with the execute rule's ID)
- [ ] Multipart skips include the `filename=` body marker
- [ ] Origin header (when used) uses `any(... [*] eq "...")` form

### Custom Rules only

- [ ] Allow-before-block ordering preserved (skip-allow rules positioned ABOVE block rules)
- [ ] Geo blocks include trusted-egress escape hatch (unless OFAC compliance block, which doesn't)
- [ ] No `js_challenge` on `/api/*` paths
- [ ] Country codes copy-pasted from Cloudflare reference, not typed

### Terraform-only (skip if not using Terraform)

- [ ] Inline `//` comment block present (ticket, peer cross-reference, per-guard rationale, approval source)
- [ ] Heredoc indentation matches neighboring rules in the same file
- [ ] File mode is `100644` (no accidental `100755`)
- [ ] `terraform fmt` is clean
- [ ] `terraform plan` reviewed by author + at least one peer; matches expected diff

### Dashboard-only (skip if not authoring via UI)

- [ ] Runbook entry created (or updated) with the same fields as the Terraform comment block; linked in the change ticket
- [ ] Change made by cloning the existing rule (if modifying), not editing it in place
- [ ] Save batched as a single logical change per Audit Log entry (no bulk reorders combined with semantic edits)
- [ ] Staging-zone dry-run completed (save in log mode in staging zone, observe 24h) before authoring in production zone
- [ ] Audit Log entry reviewed and matches expected change

### API-only (skip if not calling the Rulesets API directly)

- [ ] JSON payload committed to the versioned repo with its sibling `.md` provenance file
- [ ] Current ruleset `GET` fetched and ETag captured; `PUT` sent with `If-Match: <etag>`
- [ ] Position uses `position.before` / `position.after` with a stable rule ID (not `position.index`)
- [ ] JSON validated via the [expression test endpoint](https://developers.cloudflare.com/ruleset-engine/rulesets-api/test/) before the destructive `PUT`
- [ ] API response logged (or piped to the run-log) with the new rule's ID and timestamp
- [ ] 412 Precondition Failed handling tested (re-fetch + re-apply intent path, not blind retry)

